Atheta klagesi
is newly recorded in Alberta , British Columbia , New Brunswick , Nova Scotia , Ontario , and Prince Edward Island . In the Maritime Provinces it has frequently been recorded in old-growth and mature red spruce (
P. rubens
) forests in decomposing mushrooms, on bracket fungi, and in compost. In Québec it was recorded in yellow birch (
B. alleghaniensis
) forests by Klimaszewski et al. (2007b) .
